{{title 'Customize Help'}}
<h1>Customize Help for {{model.name}}</h1>

<div class="alert alert-warning"><b>Note:</b> Customizing a help file will override the default help with your own.  This means you will not receive automatic updates to the help file (like if a command is added/changed/corrected). Consider carefully whether you want to override the default help or just supplement it through a game-specific wiki page.
</div>

{{markdown-editor text=model.raw_contents rows=30}}

<div class="pull-right">
      <p> {{#link-to 'help-topic' model.key class="btn btn-default"}}Cancel{{/link-to}}  
      <button {{action 'save'}} class="btn btn-primary">Save</button> </p>
</div>
        
